space, plus the basis.

00:00:40.650 --> 00:00:44.670
And we saw that we could put a
variety of elements at the

00:00:44.670 --> 00:00:46.950
corners of the Bravais
lattice.

00:00:46.950 --> 00:00:49.800
And this is taken from the
archival notes where we see

00:00:49.800 --> 00:00:54.220
the simple, single atoms at the
various lattice points.

00:00:54.220 --> 00:00:58.070
And we recognized last day that
we could put clusters of

00:00:58.070 --> 00:01:00.370
atoms and so on, and
even proteins will

00:01:00.370 --> 00:01:01.580
crystallize in this form.

00:01:01.580 --> 00:01:05.650
And actually, to make a point,
about five years ago, a group

00:01:05.650 --> 00:01:09.110
